Urgent appeals for help and a R100,000 reward for information have been offered for missing student Hillary Gardee. The daughter of former EFF secretary-general Godrich Gardee disappeared on April 29. She is last known to have gone shopping at a plaza in Mbombela (Nelspruit). She was wearing a black top and black trousers and was carrying a shopping bag and a laptop carrier. Anyone with information is requested to contact 072Â 514 1456. This is a developing story. TimesLIVE